01:07.901 --> 01:10.400
So, what are you and Suzanne
doing for Christmas, John?

01:10.434 --> 01:12.534
Oh, her parents
are having a party.

01:12.567 --> 01:13.667
How about you?

01:13.701 --> 01:15.000
Oh, I don't know.

01:15.033 --> 01:16.834
Last year, I went
to a sit-down dinner

01:16.868 --> 01:17.834
for 80 people.

01:17.868 --> 01:19.968
80 People. Wow!

01:20.000 --> 01:22.567
Yeah, they got this
really long counter

01:22.601 --> 01:23.634
at Woolworth's.

01:24.667 --> 01:25.934
Merry
Christmas,
Elaine.

01:25.968 --> 01:27.734
Hey, how
you doing, Elaine?

01:27.767 --> 01:29.267
Come on.

01:29.300 --> 01:30.501
I'll take three.

01:30.534 --> 01:32.734
What's the matter with Elaine?

01:32.767 --> 01:35.968
Oh, I think it has something
to do with her ex-husband

01:36.000 --> 01:37.934
picks up the girls this morning.

01:37.968 --> 01:40.968
This is the first Christmas
she's ever spent alone.

01:41.000 --> 01:41.667
Poor thing.

01:41.701 --> 01:42.834
What a bummer.

01:42.868 --> 01:45.400
I'd go crazy if I had
to spend Christmas alone.

01:45.434 --> 01:47.100
You <i>are</i> spending
Christmas alone.

01:47.133 --> 01:48.334
I am?

01:51.133 --> 01:53.167
Well, he gave us
fair warning.

01:54.634 --> 01:57.434
$35? You call this
a day's booking?

01:57.467 --> 01:59.000
Sorry, Louie.

02:00.567 --> 02:02.567
What's
the matter
with her?

02:02.601 --> 02:04.834
You wouldn't
understand, Louie.

02:04.868 --> 02:08.067
Some people just feel
sad at Christmas.

02:08.100 --> 02:10.133
Oh, yeah?
You think I don't know that?

02:10.167 --> 02:11.267
I got feelings.

02:11.300 --> 02:12.567
Really?

02:12.601 --> 02:15.434
My mother's that way.

02:15.467 --> 02:16.834
Cries every
Christmas

02:16.868 --> 02:19.400
on account of my
little brother Nicky

02:19.434 --> 02:21.033
never comes
to see her.

02:21.067 --> 02:23.467
I'll give you
the same advice

02:23.501 --> 02:25.901
I give my mom
when she cries.

02:25.934 --> 02:29.400
I say, "Ma, shut up."

02:31.133 --> 02:33.100
I always knew you
could be tender.

02:33.133 --> 02:34.334
Yeah, only this year,

02:34.367 --> 02:36.400
I ain't going to have
any problems with Ma

02:36.434 --> 02:38.834
because Nicky's
breaking with tradition.

02:38.868 --> 02:40.067
Oh, you mean
your brother is
coming to town?

02:40.100 --> 02:41.267
Due in today.

02:41.300 --> 02:43.334
I'm expecting
him any minute.

02:43.367 --> 02:44.901
I told you
about him.

02:44.934 --> 02:46.400
Big-time
poker player,

02:46.434 --> 02:47.767
lives in
Las Vegas.

02:47.801 --> 02:48.767
Yeah, right.

02:48.801 --> 02:51.367
Always says
he's too busy
to come East.

02:51.400 --> 02:53.567
Only this year
he was in
Atlantic City

02:53.601 --> 02:54.934
to catch
the action.

02:54.968 --> 02:58.000
I talked him
into stopping by
for a few days.

02:58.033 --> 03:03.200
You know, every Christmas
Eve for the past six years

03:03.234 --> 03:06.334
Ma stayed up all night crying.

03:06.367 --> 03:08.167
It was really hard on me.

03:08.200 --> 03:09.634
I'll bet.

03:09.667 --> 03:13.467
Yeah, I hated having
to put her out in the hall.

03:18.067 --> 03:19.033
Nick!

03:19.067 --> 03:20.133
Louie!

03:20.167 --> 03:22.200
You made it, Nick!

03:28.901 --> 03:30.234
My little brother.

03:30.267 --> 03:34.467
Hey, everybody, this is
my little brother, Nicky.

03:34.501 --> 03:37.567
Ooh, I can't believe
you're here.

03:37.601 --> 03:40.200
Come here. I want
to introduce you

03:40.234 --> 03:42.067
to some of
my inferiors.

03:42.100 --> 03:44.000
Nah, we'll
do that later.

03:44.033 --> 03:46.400
Six years I haven't seen you.

03:46.434 --> 03:48.000
Let me look at you.

03:48.901 --> 03:50.133
New coat, huh?

03:51.567 --> 03:52.767
Ma can't wait
to see you.

03:52.801 --> 03:54.667
She couldn't talk
about anything else

03:54.701 --> 03:56.534
since she found out
you were coming.

03:56.567 --> 03:57.534
Right.

03:57.567 --> 03:59.334
Hey, is that
a poker game?

03:59.367 --> 04:01.667
Relax. I already told
them you're a pro.

04:01.701 --> 04:03.167
Now, listen,

04:03.200 --> 04:06.601
the sleeping arrangements
are going to be a little tricky

04:06.634 --> 04:08.834
because, you see,
we only have two beds,

04:08.868 --> 04:11.067
but Ma has trouble
sleeping anyway,

04:11.100 --> 04:13.634
so she can sit up
and you can have hers.

04:13.667 --> 04:16.399
Nicky, we're going to
have such a good time.

04:16.434 --> 04:17.834
Right, right, right.

04:17.868 --> 04:19.601
How about me sitting in
on a few hands, huh?

04:19.634 --> 04:21.968
Hey, Nick, Nicky, don't you hear
what I'm saying?

04:22.000 --> 04:24.200
Nicky, Ma's been waiting
to see you for six years.

04:24.234 --> 04:26.367
So, she can wait
a few minutes.
It won't hurt her.

04:26.400 --> 04:28.200
I ain't fooling
with you this
time, Nicky.

04:28.234 --> 04:29.200
Get up there.

04:29.234 --> 04:30.133
Hey, Jeff, get a cab

04:30.167 --> 04:31.868
and take my brother
to see my mother.

04:31.901 --> 04:33.133
Come on, Louie.
Don't push.

04:33.167 --> 04:34.634
I'm not pushing.
Now, get the hell out of here!

04:34.667 --> 04:36.100
I'm going,
I'm going.

04:36.133 --> 04:39.400
Just don't
lose all that
Christmas tip money.

04:39.434 --> 04:40.834
I want a crack at it.

04:48.968 --> 04:50.801
I know it's none of my business,
Louie, but, uh,

04:50.834 --> 04:53.167
your brother didn't seem so
anxious to visit your mother.

04:54.400 --> 04:56.767
I know.

04:56.801 --> 04:59.067
It worries me, Alex.

04:59.100 --> 05:00.701
He hurts her bad.

05:00.734 --> 05:01.834
Huh?

05:01.868 --> 05:04.634
He never shows
her any affection

05:04.667 --> 05:06.167
or consideration.

05:06.200 --> 05:10.200
Like me, I'm always saying
stuff like, "How you doing, Ma?"

05:10.234 --> 05:11.234
You know?

05:11.267 --> 05:12.567
She cooks
something,

05:12.601 --> 05:15.133
and I don't like
the way it tastes,

05:15.167 --> 05:16.734
I never spit it out.

05:16.767 --> 05:20.834
I always tell her,
"Take another crack at it."

05:20.868 --> 05:23.701
But listen,
I want to tell
you something.

05:23.734 --> 05:25.968
This is
just between
you and me.

05:26.000 --> 05:27.701
The winters have
been getting

05:27.734 --> 05:28.801
really hard on Ma,

05:28.834 --> 05:30.634
and she freezes up on me,

05:30.667 --> 05:32.167
Oh.
you know?

05:32.200 --> 05:34.501
And she needs to go someplace

05:34.534 --> 05:37.200
where it's warm
so she can thaw out.

05:37.234 --> 05:39.167
You know, like Las Vegas.

05:39.200 --> 05:39.934
Yeah.

05:39.968 --> 05:41.200
Now, here's Nick--

05:41.234 --> 05:43.767
he's got this beautiful
apartment out there.

05:43.801 --> 05:47.133
You think he ever asked her once
to come out and visit?

05:47.167 --> 05:48.133
No.

05:48.167 --> 05:49.501
Now, what I'm hoping is

05:49.534 --> 05:52.367
he's going to go home and
see how bad off she is

05:52.400 --> 05:54.868
and then get the idea
himself and ask her.

05:54.901 --> 05:56.767
That'd be swell,
but from what I saw,

05:56.801 --> 05:58.400
I wouldn't count on it, Louie.

05:58.434 --> 06:00.634
No, I'm not, I'm not.

06:00.667 --> 06:05.000
That's why I told Ma, you know,
drop a few subtle hints.

06:05.033 --> 06:06.200
Now that'd be an idea.

06:06.234 --> 06:08.667
Yeah, like I told her
to tell him,

06:08.701 --> 06:12.534
"Nicky, I'd really love to
see your apartment in Vegas

06:12.567 --> 06:14.033
"before I die,

06:14.067 --> 06:18.033
because if I don't I'll put
a curse on you from my grave."

06:18.067 --> 06:22.434
* Joy to the world,
the Lord is come *

06:22.467 --> 06:24.968
* let Earth receive
her King... *

06:25.000 --> 06:26.200
Look
at this.

06:26.234 --> 06:30.567
* Let every heart
prepare Him room *

06:30.601 --> 06:32.434
* And heaven and nature sing 

06:32.467 --> 06:34.334
* and heaven and nature sing 

06:34.367 --> 06:38.901
* And heaven and
nature sing... *

06:38.934 --> 06:41.934
Come on, give him
a buck, everybody.

06:41.968 --> 06:46.200
* Let Earth receive her King 

06:46.234 --> 06:49.968
* Let every heart
